    ROLE: Refines

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: MQTT Communications

[INTERFACE_CONTROL]
UID: IC-1
ENDPOINT: mqtts://mqtt.app.healthesolutions.ca
DIRECTION: Device in/out
PROTOCOL: MQTTs
TITLE: MQTT Broker
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall provide the MQTT broker at this address for the Device to use.
<<<

[INTERFACE_CONTROL]
UID: IC-2
DIRECTION: Device in/out
PROTOCOL: MQTTs
TITLE: Device MQTT Authentication
STATEMENT: >>>
The Device and the MQTT broker shall use mutual X.509 certificates for authentication.
<<<

[INTERFACE_CONTROL]
UID: IC-7
ENDPOINT: wss://ws-mqtt.app.healthesolutions.ca/mqtt
DIRECTION: App in/out
PROTOCOL: MQTT over Secure WebSocket
TITLE: MQTT over WebSocket
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall provide the MQTT broker at this address for the mobile app to use.
<<<

[INTERFACE_CONTROL]
UID: IC-8
DIRECTION: App in/out
PROTOCOL: HTTPS, Secure WebSocket
TITLE: App MQTT Authentication
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall authenticate a mobile app user to access a specific device via MQTT using JSON Web Tokens (JWT). The following are provided as HTTP Headers during the initial HTTPS connection to the WebSocket address before the WebSocket protocol upgrade mechanism.
<<<
SCHEMA: >>>
**x-jwt** (string)
  The JWT ID Token. Note there is no "Bearer" prefix, just the raw JWT.
**x-device-id** (string)
  The Device ID of the device to access MQTT topics for.
**x-tenant-id** (string)
  The Tenant ID of the device to access MQTT topics for.
<<<

[INTERFACE_CONTROL]
UID: IC-6
TITLE: MQTT Schema Format
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall use JSON as the interchange format for MQTT communications.
<<<

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Device State & Configuration

[INTERFACE_CONTROL]
UID: IC-4
TITLE: Bin Identifier
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall use the following integer definitions to identify a particular bin on the physical device, known as the Bin ID.
<<<
SCHEMA: >>>
- 0 - Monday PM
- 1 - Monday AM
- 2 - Tuesday PM
- 3 - Tuesday AM
- 4 - Wednesday PM
- 5 - Wednesday AM
- 6 - Thursday PM
- 7 - Thursday AM
- 8 - Friday PM
- 9 - Friday AM
- 10 - Saturday PM
- 11 - Saturday AM
- 12 - Sunday PM
- 13 - Sunday AM
<<<

[INTERFACE_CONTROL]
UID: IC-5
TITLE: Bin Status Enum
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall use the following enumeration to describe the status of a bin on the physical device. The system shall serialize the enum as its name in UPPER_CASE.
<<<
SCHEMA: >>>
**DISABLED**
  Bin is not scheduled.
**TAKEN**
  Bin has its medication taken.
**MISSED**
  Bin did not have its medication taken on time (marked as missed dose).
**PENDING**
  Bin has its medication scheduled to be taken some time in the future.
**TAKE_NOW**
  The bin's medication should be taken at the current time.
<<<

[INTERFACE_CONTROL]
UID: IC-10
TITLE: Device Event Type Enum
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall use the following enumeration to describe the different types of events on the physical device. The system shall serialize the enum as its name in UPPER_CASE.
<<<
SCHEMA: >>>
**DOOR_OPENED**
  A bin is opened.
**DOOR_CLOSED**
  A bin is closed.
**TAKEN**
  A bin's state transitions to TAKEN.
**MISSED**
  A bin's state transitions to MISSED.
**TAKE_NOW**
  A bin's state transitions to TAKE_NOW.
**RELOAD_START**
  The device's medication reload mechanism is activated.
**RELOAD_END**
  The device's medication reload mechanism has completed.
**SCHEDULE_UPDATED**
  The device's internal bin scheduling state has updated.
**PROVISIONED**
  The device has completed provisioning.
**ACTION_TIMEOUT**
  Exception condition where an action was initiated on the device but never completed (e.g., door opened but never closed, reload start but never completed).
<<<

[INTERFACE_CONTROL]
UID: IC-3
ENDPOINT: healthe/things/{THING_NAME}/state
DIRECTION: Device out
PROTOCOL: MQTTs
CONFIG: QoS 1, RETAIN
TITLE: Device State Topic Schema
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall use this topic and schema for the device's internal state.
<<<
SCHEMA: >>>
**timestamp** (integer, required)
  Unix timestamp (UTC) in milliseconds.
**battery** (integer)
  Battery percentage, out of 100.
**charging** (boolean)
  Battery charging status.
**reloading** (boolean)
  If the device is currently reloading medication.
**doors** (integer)
  An integer acting as a bitfield to track door states. Each bit corresponds to a specific bin door, read from the Least Significant Bit (LSB) upwards. 1 = door open, 0 = door closed.
**bins** (array of objects)
    **id** (integer, required)
      Bin ID on the physical device reporting the state.
    **status** (string, required)
      The status of the bin, serialized as the name of the Bin Status enum.
    **scheduled_time** (integer)
      Unix timestamp (UTC) in milliseconds of the scheduled time the medication in this bin is taken at.
    **event_time** (integer)
      Unix timestamp (UTC) in milliseconds of the last recorded update to this bin's state.
<<<

[INTERFACE_CONTROL]
UID: IC-9
ENDPOINT: healthe/things/{THING_NAME}/event
DIRECTION: Device out
PROTOCOL: MQTTs
CONFIG: QoS 1
TITLE: Device Event Topic Schema
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall use this topic and schema to report device events.
<<<
SCHEMA: >>>
**timestamp** (integer, required)
  Unix timestamp (UTC) in milliseconds that the event was observed/recorded.
**event_type** (string, required)
  The type of event, serialized as the name of the Device Event Type enum.
**bin_id** (integer)
  Bin ID on the physical device reporting the event (if the event is associated with a bin).
**meta** (object)
  Additional event type specific metadata.
<<<

[INTERFACE_CONTROL]
UID: IC-12
TITLE: Device Event Action Timeout Type Enum
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall use the following enumeration to describe the different types of `ACTION_TIMEOUT` events. The system shall serialize the enum as its name in UPPER_CASE.
<<<
SCHEMA: >>>
**DOOR_LEFT_OPEN**
  A bin door is opened but not closed within a certain period of time.
**RELOAD_TIMEOUT**
  Medication reload is initiated but not completed within a certain period of time.
<<<

[INTERFACE_CONTROL]
UID: IC-11
TITLE: Device Event Action Timeout Metadata
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall use this schema to report additional information for `ACTION_TIMEOUT` events.
<<<
SCHEMA: >>>
**timeout_type** (string, required)
  The type of event, serialized as the name of the Event Action Timeout Type enum.
**duration** (integer, required)
  Milliseconds that elapsed triggering the timeout.
**event_type** (string)
  The type of event that marked the start of the timeout, serialized as the name of the Device Event Type enum
**start_time** (integer)
  Unix timestamp (UTC) in milliseconds of the event that started the timeout timer.
<<<

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Provisioning

[INTERFACE_CONTROL]
UID: IC-14
DIRECTION: App to/from device
PROTOCOL: Unified Provisioning / Bluetooth LE
TITLE: Device Unified Provisioning
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall use ESP32 Unified Provisioning over Bluetooth Low Energy to exchange data between the mobile app and the device during provisioning.
<<<

[INTERFACE_CONTROL]
UID: IC-17
DIRECTION: Device in/out
PROTOCOL: MQTTs
TITLE: IoT Core Fleet Provisioning
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall use IoT Core Fleet Provisioning to exchange temporary claim credentials and certificate for permanent X.509 certificates.
<<<

[INTERFACE_CONTROL]
UID: IC-18
DIRECTION: Device in/out
PROTOCOL: MQTTs / mTLS
TITLE: IoT Core Fleet Provisioning Request
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall use the parameters for a device to request permanent Fleet Provisioning certificates.
<<<
SCHEMA: >>>
**Connection level:** Claim certificate X.509 key pair

**Fleet provisioning parameters:**

**SerialNumber** (string, required)
  The serial number of the device.
**ClaimId** (string, required)
  The claim identifier, from the Device Claim Token.
**claimToken** (string, required)
  The claim token value, from the Device Claim Token.
<<<

[INTERFACE_CONTROL]
UID: IC-13
ENDPOINT: device_serial
DIRECTION: App to device
PROTOCOL: Unified Provisioning
TITLE: Device Serial Endpoint
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall define the endpoint for the app to request the serial number of a device.
<<<
SCHEMA: >>>
**Input:** (empty)

**Output:** JSON object

**serialNumber** (string, required)
  The serial number of the device.
<<<

[INTERFACE_CONTROL]
UID: IC-15
DIRECTION: App to device
TITLE: Device Claim Token
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall use the schema to describe a temporary claim credential during provisioning.
<<<
SCHEMA: >>>
**claimId** (string, required)
  The claim identifier for this provisioning request.
**claimToken** (string, required)
  The claim token, a shared secret to authenticate the request.
<<<

[INTERFACE_CONTROL]
UID: IC-16
ENDPOINT: device_claim_token_set
DIRECTION: App to device
PROTOCOL: Unified Provisioning
TITLE: Device Claim Token Set Endpoint
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall define the endpoint for the app to provide the device a temporary claim credential to the device during provisioning.
<<<
SCHEMA: >>>
**Input:** JSON serialized Device Claim Token

**Output:** (empty)
<<<

[[/SECTION]]
